I have re-installed tensorflow=1.0.1 and it gave me the same error. But this time I installed it without anaconda environment and with python2.7.
Further, I came across that the the tensorflow api has changed and so I had to do a
git checkout master
in /models/ directory
and this worked.

body:
I have re-installed tensorflow=1.0.1 and it gave me the same error. But this time I installed it without anaconda environment and with python2.7.
Further, I came across that the the tensorflow api has changed and so I had to do a 
`git checkout master` 
in /models/ directory 
and this worked.
